  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "O wondrous type! O vision fair Of glory that the Church may share, Which Christ upon the mountain shows, where brighter than the sun He glows!",
    "v2": "From age to age the tale declare, How with the three disciples there, Where Moses and Eli- jah meet, The Lord holds converse high and sweet.",
    "v3": "The law and prophets there have place, Two chosen witnesses of grace; The Father&#39;s voice from out the cloud proclaims His only Son aloud.",
    "v4": "With shining face and bright array, Christ deigns to mani- fest today What glory shall be theirs above who joy in God with perfect love.",
    "v5": "And faithful hearts are raised on high by this great vision&#39;s mystery; For which in joyful strains we raise the voice of prayer, the hymn of praise."
  },
